25|$|Initially, the <b>Slovak</b> <b>koruna</b> was at {{par with}} the Bohemian and Moravian koruna, with 10 korunas = 1 Reichsmark. It was devalued, on 1 October 1940, to a rate of 11.62 Slovak korunas to one Reichsmark, while {{the value of the}} Bohemian and Moravian {{currency}} remained unchanged against the Reichsmark.|$|E
